Text: My main achievements for last week was improving the interface and adding little modifications in an attempt to improve the experience.
It has been a fun experience, no complaints really.
But if we're talking about room for improvement - I need to work on trusting the process a little more.
I feel this underlying 'doom' in my gut.
I suppose it is because this is our last shot at the studio projects - I am wanting it to be as rewarding and worthwhile as it can be.
The impending 'doom' must just be the pressure to do as much as I can before the initiation of the internship placement.
Perhaps, it is excitement.
They sometimes do say that nervousness and excitement are similar.
Regardless, my personal takeaways from last week is to enjoy the project and 'trust the process'.
I have got an amazing team that I can trust as well.
On topic of the team, the team dynamic is going good.
I feel that the team reflections work for our dynamic in particular because everyone embodies investment and respect to the project.
However, I am finding that sometimes some team members discuss project matters amongst themselves, despite it being relevant for all team members.
I mention this as a potential issue because inclusion is very important for a strong team.
One of our team rules is that we 'make decisions' together.

In an attempt to counter the exclusion, I have not officially mentioned this in our team reflections - but have passively asked team members in the moment what they were talking about so there would be an opportunity to share to the group.
If this persists, perhaps mentioning it in our next team reflection would be worthwhile.
Not going to lie, sometimes I feel that I may be too pushy towards the team in terms of communication.
I am aware that my language can be a little too blunt or straightforward.
Definitely in need of working on my tone - perhaps something kinder with some softer qualities will be effective.
